experiments.name: PBMC mass cytometry time-course (Fig 2, Bodenmiller et al., 2012). Median statistics exported 1/23/2014 by Jonathan Karr from Cytobank community site experiment #26932.

description: Human peripheral blood mononuclear cell (PBMC) immune signaling colored with mass cytometry data collected at eight timepoints (0, 1, 5, 15, 30, 60, 120, 240 min) post LPS induction (Bodenmiller et al., 2012). PBMC's are a critical component of the immune system, helping fight infection and adapt to intruders. The animated pathway diagram highlights the differential cell type responses observed by Bodenmiller et al. Heatmaps indicate each node's median activity for the fourteen observed cell types (first row: CD14- monocytes; second row CD14 monocytes; third row: denritic cells, IgM B cells, IgM- B cells, NK cells; last row: CD8 T cells, CD4 T cells). Nodes are colored by their mean value across all fourteen cell types. Yellow color indicates high activity; blue indicates low activity. Diagram modified from Figure S6 of Bodenmiller et al. References • Bodenmiller, B. et al. Multiplexed mass cytometry profiling of cellular states perturbed by small-molecule regulators. Nat. Biotechnol., 30, 858-867 (2012).
